The paper discusses the implementation and utilization of a tool for constrained interaction testing, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The tool, Avocado, employs computational algorithms and a constraint solver, which suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of a test oracle, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
